cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper is about training deep networks for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses unsupervised domain adaptation, which involves learning from data in a different domain than the one the model was trained on. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses generating proxy labels for the target domain, which involves natural language processing techniques, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses datasets related to autonomous driving, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
